ts%20are%20among%20the%20key%20issues%20for%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%20however%2C%20always%20supported%20a%20merit-based%20legal%20immigration%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20want%20to%20do%20and%20what%20I%20will%20do%20is%20--you%20graduate%20from%20a%20college%2C%20I%20think%20you%20should%20get%20a%20Green%20Card%20automatically%20as%20part%20of%20your%20diploma%2C%20a%20Green%20Card%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20this%20country.%20And%20that%20includes%20junior%20colleges%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%2C%2078%2C%20said%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BAll-In%26quot%3B%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Green%20Card%2C%20known%20officially%20as%20a%20permanent%20resident%20card%2C%20is%20an%20identity%20document%20showing%20a%20person%20has%20permanent%20residency%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20podcast%20was%20hosted%20by%20four%20venture%20capitalists%3A%20Chamath%20Palihapitiya%2C%20Jason%20Calacanis%2C%20David%20Sacks%2C%20and%20David%20Friedberg%2C%20three%20of%20whom%20are%20immigrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20remarks%20came%20as%20he%20was%20pressed%20by%20Calacanis%20to%20%26quot%3Bpromise%20us%20you%20will%20give%20us%20more%20ability%20to%20import%20the%20best%20and%20brightest%20around%20the%20world%20to%20America.%26quot%3B%20Trump%2C%20the%20presumptive%20candidate%20from%20the%20Republican%20Party%2C%20also%20lamented%20%26quot%3Bstories%20where%20people%20graduated%20from%20a%20top%20college%20or%20from%20a%20college%2C%20and%20they%20desperately%20wanted%20to%20stay%20here%2C%20they%20had%20a%20plan%20for%20a%20company%2C%20a%20concept%2C%20and%20they%20can't%20-%20they%20go%20back%20to%20India%2C%20they%20go%20back%20to%20China%2C%20they%20do%20the%20same%20basic%20company%20in%20those%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...and%20they%20become%20multi-billionaires%20employing%20thousands%20and%20thousands%20of%20people%2C%20and%20it%20could%20have%20been%20done%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet%20me%20just%20tell%20you%20that%20it's%20so%20sad%20when%20we%20lose%20people%20from%20Harvard%2C%20MIT%2C%20from%20the%20greatest%20schools.%20and%20lesser%20schools%20that%20are%20phenomenal%20schools%20also.%20And%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%20and%20I%20would%20have%20done%20this%2C%20but%20then%20we%20had%20to%20solve%20the%20COVID%20problem%20because%20that%20came%20in%20and%2C%20you%20know%2C%20sort%20of%20dominated%20for%20a%20little%20while%2C%20as%20you%20perhaps%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20in%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20reiterated%20his%20first-term%20policy%2C%20about%20foreign%20students%20getting%20a%20Green%20Card%20after%20receiving%20a%20degree%20from%20a%20higher%20education%20institution%20in%20the%20STEM%20(science%2C%20technology%2C%20engineering%2C%20and%20math)%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnybody%20graduates%20from%20a%20college%2C%20you%20go%20in%20there%20for%20two%20years%20or%20four%20years%2C%20If%20you%20graduate%20or%20you%20get%20a%20doctorate%20degree%20from%20a%20college%2C%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20this%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20force%20the%20brilliant%20people%2C%20the%20people%20that%20graduate%20from%20college%2C%20the%20people%20that%20are%20number%20one%20in%20their%20class%20from%20the%20best%20colleges%2C%20you%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20recruit%20these%20people%20and%20keep%20the%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomebody%20graduates%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20class%3B%20they%20can't%20even%20make%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20company%20because%20they%20don't%20think%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20going%20to%20end%20on%20day%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20latest%20annual%20Open%20Doors%20report%20of%20the%20Institute%20of%20International%20Education%20more%20than%20a%20million%20international%20students%20from%20more%20than%20210%20places%20of%20origin%20are%20studying%20at%20US%20higher%20education%20institutions%20during%20the%202022-23%20academic%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20remained%20the%20top-sending%20country%20in%202022%2F23%2C%20with%20289%2C526%20students%20studying%20in%20the%20U.S.%20But%20students%20from%20China%20saw%20a%20slight%20decline%20of%200.2%20per%20cent%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20the%20second%20largest%20sending%20country%2C%20reached%20an%20all-time%20high%20of%20268%2C923%20international%20students%20in%202022%2F23%2C%20an%20increase%20of%2035%20per%20cent%20as%20against%20the%20previous%20year.%20Overall%2053%20per%20cent%20of%20all%20international%20students%20in%202022%2F23%20were%20from%20China%20and%20India%2C%20comparable%20to%20the%20prior%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20market%20share%20for%20each%20place%20of%20origin%20has%20shifted%2C%20with%2027%20per%20cent%20of%20students%20from%20China%20and%2025%20per%20cent%20of%20students%20from%20India%2C%20in%20comparison%20to%2033%20per%20cent%20from%20China%20and%2018%20per%20cent%20from%20India%20in%202017-18.%20Trump's%20latest%20comments%20stood%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20immigration%20policy%20he%20adopted%20while%20in%20office%20and%20were%20a%20direct%20overture%20to%20wealthy%20business%20leaders%20whom%20he%20is%20courting%20as%20donors%20and%20supporters%20of%20his%20campaign%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20had%20at%20times%20sought%20to%20reform%20the%20nation's%20immigration%20system%20to%20scale%20back%20family-based%20immigration%20and%20to%20prioritise%20wealthy%20immigrants%2C%20who%20had%20valuable%20work%20skills%20or%20who%20were%20highly%20educated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20during%20his%20term%20as%20president%2C%20Trump's%20immigration%20agenda%20included%20restrictions%20on%20green%20cards%2C%20visa%20programmes%2C%20refugee%20resettlement%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20legal%20immigration%2C%20significantly%20reducing%20the%20number%20of%20lawful%20permanent%20residents%20entering%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20began%20his%20presidency%20by%20signing%20an%20executive%20order%20that%20banned%20travellers%20from%20seven%20predominantly%20Muslim%20countries%20and%20later%20embraced%20a%20proposal%20to%20cut%20legal%20immigration%20by%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20his%20presidency%2C%20Trump%20assailed%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20programme%2C%20favoured%20by%20tech%20companies%20as%20a%20way%20to%20hire%20foreign%20skilled%20workers%2C%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btheft%20of%20American%20prosperity.%26quot%3B%20The%20H-1B%20visa%20is%20a%20non-immigrant%20visa%20that%20allows%20US%20companies%20to%20employ%20foreign%20workers%20in%20speciality%20occupations%20that%20require%20theoretical%20or%20technical%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETechnology%20companies%20depend%20on%20it%20to%20hire%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20employees%20each%20year%20from%20countries%20like%20India%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20expanded%20restrictions%20on%20legal%20immigration%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20his%20last%20year%20in%20office%20and%20had%20proposed%20suspending%20all%20immigration%20to%20the%20United%20States%20and%20deporting%20foreign%20students%20if%20they%20did%20not%20attend%20at%20least%20some%20classes%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20month%20before%20the%202020%20election%2C%20Trump%20again%20moved%20to%20restrict%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20programme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719053280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Ftrbnmngo_donald-trump_625x300_02_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2